Added and updated.

Maybe it is my mistake, you can see my comment that the #25 is passed the test case. But I also request about the correction of timercmp() in patch set #25. Which cause you're changing in patch set #26. 😞

I think we should not drop the negation, in the description about timercmp():
```
Some systems (but not Linux/glibc), have a broken timercmp() implementation, in which CMP of >=, <=, and == do not work; portable applications can instead use
!timercmp(..., <) !timercmp(..., >) !timercmp(..., !=)
```

> Maybe it is my mistake, you can see my comment that the #25 is passed the test case. But I also request about the correction of timercmp() in patch set #25. Which cause you're changing in patch set #26.

Yeah, no doubt I messed something up there. My apologies.

> I think we should not drop the negation, in the description about timercmp():

I think we should assume that we're not operating with a broken `timercmp()` implementation. If someone wants to run libpldm on a platform that has such a broken implementation then they can fix it then. Let's keep the code simple to understand, we've already messed it up once 😊
Done
Please don't line-wrap this one, it's easier for the tooling if it's just all one the one line, even if it's long.
Done

Note that I said:

> in a line immediately above your Signed-off-by: ...:

That means no blank line here. git has tools for processing the "trailer" paragraph:

https://git-scm.com/docs/git-interpret-trailers

We want that tooling to work.
Done

transport: Correct comparison in while loop condition
